<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="lack-n">lack <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /læk/    美 /læk/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-shortage">1.<strong>缺乏；不足 (shortage)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>(a) lack of</strong> food / money / sleep / skills
缺乏食物/金钱/睡眠/技能</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These children have health problems linked to poor diet and <strong>a lack of</strong> exercise.
这些孩子有与不良饮食和缺乏运动相关的健康问题。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="for-lack-of">for lack of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>因缺少：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The tour was cancelled for lack of bookings. 
这次出游因无人预订而取消了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The leaves turned yellow for lack of light.
由于缺少光照，叶子变黄了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>More and more high-rise buildings have been built in big cities <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (因缺少) space.  （2010 福建改）  </li>
<li>Health problems are closely connected with bad eating habits and <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (缺乏) exercise.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. for lack of  2. a lack of  </p></div>